@c This file is include from install.texi and contains the descriptions for
@c package-specific enable/disable and with/without options

In addition, the following @command{configure} options, specific to the
@value{PACKAGE_TITLE} package are available:

@table @command

@item --enable-streams-syncqs
@opindex streams-syncqs
When enabled, MP syncrhonization queues are enabled for SMP kernels.
This option defaults to @samp{disabled}.
This option is not tested for early releases.

@item --disable-streams-kthreads
@opindex streams-kthreads
When enabled, the STREAMS scheduler runs as a kernel thread.  When disabled, the STREAMS scheduler
runs as a software interrupt (bottom half).
Running the STREAMS scheduler at bottom half instead of a kernel thread breaks the @file{strinet}
driver, which must be able to invoke kernel functions that might sleep (but don't).
This option defaults to @samp{enabled}.

@item --disable-streams-utils
@opindex streams-utils
I have experimented with putting the STREAMS utilities into their own package, @file{strutil},
however, this is not complete yet.
This option defaults to @samp{enabled}.
Do not disable this option.

@item --disable-big-compile
@opindex big-compile
When enabled, the STREAMS, the Stream head, and the clone driver are all compiled together in one
big compilation unit.  This allows the compiler greater opportunity to optimize.
This option defaults to @samp{enabled}.
Do not disable this option.

@item --enable-module-sth
@opindex module-sth
Enable @file{sth} (stream head) module linked into @file{streams} object.
The default is to create the module as a separate loadable kernel module,
unless option @samp{big-compile} is specified.
This option defaults to @samp{disabled}.
This option defaults to @samp{enabled} if @samp{big-compile} is enabled.

