This option defaults to @samp{disabled}.
This option is not tested.  Do not enable this option yet.

@item --disable-streams-bcm
@opindex streams-bcm
Disable STREAMS binary compatibility mode.
When enabled, exported functions (and callouts) will always pass three arguments in registers on
architectures supporting @code{regparm} (i.e. @var{__i386__}, @var{__x86_64__}, @var{__k8__})
regardless of how the kernel was compiled.
This option defaults to @samp{enabled}.

